  <span id="freeText5707525603634756836" style="display:none">My third Faulkner novel (other two being The Sound And The Fury and As I Lay Dying). Expectations were very high, and I was not disappointed. It was better than As I Lay Dying, but not good enough to overthrow TSATF from its trone. 4.8 stars. It worked really well for me until the last chapter, which I found to be very confusing and because of it I gave it 4.8 and not 5.0 rating. Overall, if you love Faulkner this is a book for you. It is not as complicated or allegorical like TSATF or As I Lay Dying, but it is Faulkner, which means it is still very very good. And again a proof that William Cuthbert Faulkner is THE best writer of the 20th century.</span>
